-- Obama pressed Hu on currency, economic rebalancing
-- 
-- Sun Nov 13, 2011 12:28am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/11/13/us-apec-obama-china-currency-idUSTRE7AC06420111113

 

 HONOLULU  (Reuters) - President Barack Obama pressed Chinese President Hu Jintao to allow its currency to rise and on the need for a rebalancing in the global economy during their meeting on Saturday, senior White House officials said. 
 Obama also cautioned Hu that Americans were becoming impatient over U.S.-China economic ties, said the officials. (Reporting by  Caren Bohan ; Editing by  Peter Cooney )